'''Juan Olivares''' (born February 20, 1941) is a former [[Chile|Chilean]] [[association football|football]] goalkeeper, who played for the [[Chile national football team|Chile national team]] between 1965 and 1974, gaining 33 caps. He was part of the Chile squad for the [[1966 FIFA World Cup|1966]] and [[1974 FIFA World Cup|1974]] world cups.

At club level, Olivares played for [[Santiago Wanderers]], [[Club Deportivo Magallanes|Magallanes]], [[Cobreloa]] and [[Uni<U+00F3>n Espa<U+00F1>ola]].

